data.name: label9.Text
data.value:
Instruction:
1. Make a calibration screenshot. 2. Select some part of the screen. (You can do this by dragging the selection region on the image.) 3. Select the output folder. 4. Begin the process. You can stop and restart it at any time.
The part of the screen will be saved only if its downsampled version differs by the selected percent of pixels from the previous one.

Instruction:
1. Select files to cut a part from. 2. Select some part of the screen. (You can do this by dragging the selection region on the image or by providing exact values in input fields) 3. Select the output folder. 4. Begin the process.
